'Yan Republican sun yi wa mata barazanar kada kuri'a kafin zaben ta tsakiya da Kavanaugh, masu bincike sun yi gargadin
Tun da yawancin manyan 'yan siyasa a cikin 'yan Republican suna goyon bayan kuma suna kare babban takarar majalisa Brett Kavanaugh, wanda ya sami ƙarin zargin cin zarafin jima'i da aka yi wa kansa, masu bincike sun yi gargadin cewa za su sami motsi, musamman daga mata, a cikin zaɓen gida na gaba.
A halin yanzu, yawancin 'yan jam'iyyar Republican sun riga sun ba da alamun cewa suna son ci gaba da jefa kuri'a.
Waɗannan abubuwa ba za a iya janye su ba, in ji Grant Reeher, wani farfesa a fannin kimiyyar siyasa a Makarantar Maxwell ta Jami'ar Syracuse, zuwa The Hill a wata kasida da aka wallafa a ranar Asabar.
Reeher ya ce yana shakkar cewa Sanata Jeff Flakes (R-Arizona) na FBI na karshe zai iya kwantar da hankalin masu jefa kuri'a.
'Yan mata ba za su manta da abubuwan da suka faru a jiya ba, ba za su manta da hakan ba gobe ba, ba a watan Nuwamba ba,' in ji Karine Jean-Pierre, wani babban mai ba da shawara da kuma mai magana da yawun 'yan sanda na kungiyar MoveOn a ranar Juma'a, a cewar jaridar Washington, D.C.
A safiyar Juma'a, masu zanga-zangar sun rera waƙa cewa "November is coming!" yayin da suke zanga-zangar a cikin Senate lokacin da 'yan jam'iyyar Republican da ke kula da kwamitin shari'a suka zaɓi ci gaba da zaben Kavanaugh duk da cewa an ba da shaida ga Dr. Christine Blasey Ford, in ji Mic.
"Ƙarfafawa da kuma sha'awar 'yan siyasa za su yi fashewa", in ji Stu Rothenberg, wani mai bincike na siyasa mai zaman kansa.
